  "body": "Hello,\r\nI am trying to migrate a contract using pure Javascript.\r\n\r\n```\r\nstatic async deploy(contractName,args){  \r\n    const filePath = path.resolve('build/contracts/'+contractName+'.json');\r\n    let rawdata = fs.readFileSync(filePath);\r\n    const  contractArtifacts = JSON.parse(rawdata); \r\n    const newContract = contract(contractArtifacts);\r\n    newContract.setProvider(web3Provider)\r\n    const newInstance = await newContract.new(...args,{from:\"0x627306090abaB3A6e1400e9345bC60c78a8BEf57\",gas:\"0\"});\r\n   \r\n    return newInstance;\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nThe expected output was a new instance but I got this error:\r\n`    Returned error: The method eth_sendTransaction is not supported. Use eth_sendRawTransaction to send a signed transaction to Besu.\r\n`\r\nSo I tried to uses web3 instead of .new()\r\n```\r\nconst newInstance =  await new web3.eth.Contract(contractArtifacts.abi)\r\n\t\t.deploy({\r\n      data:\"0x016f9712d43c175150d9328712c41aa34cbc65815eda38f9aa7fc2abb3e5b2d3\",\r\n\t\t\targuments: args\r\n\t\t})\r\n\t\t.send({\r\n\t\t\tfrom: '0x627306090abaB3A6e1400e9345bC60c78a8BEf57',\r\n\t\t\tgas: '0'\r\n\t\t});\r\n    return newInstance;\r\n```\r\nBut it gave me the same error. Could you please tell me what this error mean? and how to solve it?\r\nThanks in advance.",
