    "body": "Hello @timbeiko ,\r\nI tried to make a raw transaction by following this [tutorial](https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/1.2.0/Using-Pantheon/Transactions/Transactions/) \r\n```\r\n static async deploy(contractName,args,private_key){  \r\n    const filePath = path.resolve('build/contracts/'+contractName+'.json');\r\n    let rawdata = fs.readFileSync(filePath);\r\n    const  contractArtifacts = JSON.parse(rawdata); \r\n    const addressFrom = web3.eth.accounts.privateKeyToAccount(private_key).address;\r\n    const contractData = contractArtifacts.bytecode;\r\n    web3.eth.getTransactionCount(addressFrom, \"pending\").then((txnCount) => {\r\n      // Create the contract creation transaction object\r\n      var txObject = {\r\n         arguments:args,\r\n         nonce: web3.utils.toHex(txnCount),\r\n         gasPrice: 0,\r\n         gas: \"0x1ffffffffffffe\",\r\n         data: contractData\r\n      };\r\n      var tx = new ethTx(txObject);\r\n      const privateKey = Buffer.from(private_key,'hex');\r\n      tx.sign(privateKey);\r\n      var serializedTx = tx.serialize();\r\n      var rawTxHex = '0x' + serializedTx.toString('hex');\r\n      web3.eth.sendSignedTransaction(rawTxHex)\r\n      .on('receipt', receipt => { console.log('Receipt: ', receipt); })\r\n      .catch(error => { console.log('Error: ', error.message); });\r\n    })\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then test it\r\n```\r\nconst test = async()=>{\r\n    await contractClass.deploy('VirusToken',[\"yarab\",\"yta\",0],'7af1e61aa083d038474bdf1ec59620c6431d710858d7a8436389713f2adf3d8f');\r\n}\r\n```\r\nIt gave me this error\r\n`Error:  Returned error: Invalid params`  \r\nWhat am I doing wrong?  Thanks.",
